# Disable ALL line-ending normalisation. This is not a style preference — it is required
# for correctness.
#
# The launcher verifies every payload file against a SHA-256 in manifest.json. If Git
# normalises LF<->CRLF, a file checked out on one machine differs byte-for-byte from the same
# file on another, so New-Manifest.ps1 would record hashes that do not match what
# raw.githubusercontent.com actually serves — and every player's sync would fail its
# checksum, repeatedly, with no obvious cause.
#
# Treating everything as binary keeps working copy, stored blob, and served bytes identical.
* -text

# Belt and braces for the payload specifically.
payload/** -text -diff
